 This is api collection link:->
 		"https://www.getpostman.com/collections/309ba099c71d7ac7dc0e"

 Apis Name :
   	1) User
   		a)register:- Create new user ParamName like(fistName,lastName,email,password,countryCode,mobileNo,userName).Note:-userName is not mandatory if userName doesn't get so i have internaly manage userName assign firstName.
   		b)login:- Login User ParamName like(userName/email, password). we can use userName or email 
   	2) Post 
   		a) createPost:- Create new post ParamName(userId,postTitle,token).
   		b) getAllPosts:-Get all post by userId ParamName(userId,token).
   		c) getSinglePostInfo:Get all  information like(allcomments and like in this post) about particular post ParamName(postId,userId,token).
   		d) commentOnPost:- Comment on perticular post ParamName(comment,postId,userId,token).
   		e) likePost:-LikeOrDisLike post ParmName(for likePost-> isLike:1 or for 	disLikePost-> isLike:0,postId,userId,token).Note Api name same for like or dislike. 
   	3) Chat
   		getChannelById:- Get all information about channel ParamName(userId,token,channelId).
   		getUserSearch:- User search ParamName(userId,token,search).

   		a)Created events for one to one chat:-
   			i) connection and disconnection events to log when a user connected and left
   			ii) create and fire custom events using the "socket.emit" function like (chatMessage,online,ofline);
	   		iii)(chatMessage,online,ofline) these emit events from clients then sever handle these events using "socket.on" function.
	   		iV) create one event in server side to send the response to client using "io.emit" like(chatMessage).
	   	b) created events for one to multiple chat.
	   		i) connection and disconnection events to log when a user connected and left
   			ii) create and fire custom events using the "socket.emit" function like (createChannel,createMessage);
	   		iii)(createChannel,createMessage) these emit events from clients then sever handle these events using "socket.on" function.